WorkItem.Description:
Concerning this example:
OData.read("http://odata.netflix.com/v1/Catalog/Genres", function (data, response) {
 
//success handler
 
       });
 
How would one append header information to the request?  In my case, I need to include authorization and other custom values required by my ODATA service.

Comments.Message:
The OData.read() function takes either a string or an object as its first argument:  

OData.read({ requestUri: "http://odata.netflix.com/v1/Catalog/Genres",
  headers: { Accept: "application/json" } },
  function (data, response) {
    alert("Operation succeeded.");
  }, function (err) {
    alert("Error occurred " + err.message);
  });
